    <h1>History of Communicator Drivers</h1>

    <h2 id="kp-db-import">DB Import</h2>
    <pre>KpDbImport 5.0.3.0 (May 17, 2021)
- Updated DB connectors

KpDbImport 5.0.2.0 (June 23, 2020)
- The password in the configuration file is encrypted

KpDbImport 5.0.1.0 (August 29, 2019)
- Supports commands for changing data in the database

KpDbImport 5.0.0.0 (December 26, 2018)
- Initial development of the driver
</pre>

    <h2 id="kp-email">Email</h2>
    <pre>KpEmail 5.0.4.0 (May 17, 2021)
- Separated username and sender address

KpEmail 5.0.3.0 (December 14, 2020)
- Update due to changes in the base libraries

KpEmail 5.0.2.0 (June 23, 2020)
- The password in the configuration file is encrypted

KpEmail 5.0.1.1 (January 28, 2020)
- Supports default network credentials without a password

KpEmail 5.0.1.0 (August 29, 2019)
- Sending emails with attachments
</pre>

    <h2 id="kp-http-notif">HTTP Notifications</h2>
    <pre>KpHttpNotif 5.0.1.1 (On hold)
- Added address separator option

KpHttpNotif 5.0.1.0 (December 14, 2020)
- POST method support
</pre>

    <h2 id="kp-modbus">Modbus</h2>
    <pre>KpModbus 5.1.3.1 (November 15, 2021)
- Fixed data packet format for multiple commands
  Warning: no backward compatibility for multiple commands having elements of 4 bytes or more

KpModbus 5.1.3.0 (May 17, 2021)
- Improved the flexibility of classes that implement the communication protocol

KpModbus 5.1.2.0 (January 28, 2020)
- Transaction IDs are increased in the Modbus TCP mode

KpModbus 5.1.1.1 (June 03, 2019)
- Fixed bug of sending commands if there are several devices on communication line

KpModbus 5.1.1.0 (December 26, 2018)
- Refactoring to simplify development of derived drivers

KpModbus 5.1.0.3 (July 30, 2018)
- Absolute template path support

KpModbus 5.1.0.2 (March 16, 2018)
- Localization of the file filters is fixed
</pre>

    <h2 id="kp-modbus-slave">Modbus Slave</h2>
    <pre>KpModbusSlave 5.0.0.1 (November 15, 2021)
- Update due to changes in KpModbus

KpModbusSlave 5.0.0.0 (June 23, 2020)
- Initial development of the driver
</pre>

    <h2 id="kp-opc">OPC</h2>
    <pre>KpOpc 5.0.3.0 (December 14, 2020)
- Update due to changes in the base libraries

KpOpc 5.0.2.0 (March 16, 2018)
- Date and time tags are supported
- The array checkbox is made inactive for clarity
</pre>

    <h2 id="kp-opc-ua">OPC UA</h2>
    <pre>KpOpcUa 5.0.0.2 (November 15, 2021)
- Fixed saving security options

KpOpcUa 5.0.0.1 (May 17, 2021)
- Fixed a bug when browsing OPC server nodes

KpOpcUa 5.0.0.0 (January 28, 2020)
- Initial development of the driver
</pre>

    <h2 id="kp-snmp">SNMP</h2>
    <pre>KpSnmp 5.0.2.0 (December 14, 2020)
- Update due to changes in the base libraries

KpSnmp 5.0.1.0 (January 28, 2020)
- Possible to specify the configuration file name in the device command line
</pre>

    <h2 id="kp-telegram">Telegram</h2>
    <pre>KpTelegram 5.0.2.0 (December 14, 2020)
- Update due to changes in the base libraries

KpTelegram 5.0.1.1 (June 23, 2020)
- Fixed working with TLS on Windows 7
- Computer code is saved in the storage directory

KpTelegram 5.0.1.0 (June 28, 2019)
- Adding subscriptions using the form
- The Registration tab works in new Administrator
</pre>
